gomodel:SYNGO_5428  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6: electron microscopy showed CRF (gene CRH, Corticotropin-releasing hormone, aka. Corticotropin-releasing factor) and its receptor CRFr (gene CRHR1) localized to synapses. Within presynaptic terminals, CRF/CRH was mostly localized to dense core vesicles.\n\n\"Reversal of the markers using immunogold for CRF and immunoperoxidase for detection of CRFr showed less extensive coexpression. This may reflect the limited immunogold penetration in large dense core vesicles (dcv's), the organelles most commonly showing CRF immunoperoxidase reaction product in axon terminals.\". Experimental description: Results, Figure 6 legend: \"Immunogold labeling for CRFr and CRF-immunoperoxidase reaction product in dendrites (A,B) and somata (C,D) in rat CeL In\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5428" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

